COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xe4
STRING: I was absentmindedly gazing down the hallway from
the cafeteria when I noticed one of the teachers start
talking to Fal.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xfa
STRING: And then give her something that looked like a bundle
of papers.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x106
STRING: So it happened again, huh?

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x112
STRING: My suspicions aroused, I stood up and left Torta at the
table.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x11e
STRING: [Chris] “I have to go do something.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x150
STRING: [Torta] “Out in the hallway?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x166
STRING: [Chris] “Sorry, I'll be back in a sec, okay?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x198
STRING: [Torta] “Oh...

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1c6
STRING: Okay.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1f4
STRING: I left Torta, and deep inside my heart apologized to
someone else who wasn't at the table.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x20a
STRING: I decided not to think too deeply about who it was.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x21e
STRING: [Chris] “Fal?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x234
STRING: I ran just a little to catch up to her, and when I did,
she turned about with a slightly perplexed smile on her
face.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x24a
STRING: And for just an instant, that expression seemed more
serious than it did last time.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x256
STRING: [Chris] “Fal...?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x290
STRING: [Fal] “Oh...

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x2be
STRING: Hi Chris.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x2ca
STRING: But that thought I'd had was just for an instant, as Fal
called my name with her usual smile.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x2e0
STRING: I didn't think it was just my imagination, however...

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x2ec
STRING: [Chris] “Did you get asked to do something again?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x31e
STRING: [Fal] “Oh... Yes, yes I did.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x334
STRING: [Chris] “Sounds like it's going to be a tough one.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x366
STRING: [Fal] “Umm...

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x394
STRING: Oh yes, quite tough.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x3a0
STRING: She peered up at me as she spoke.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x3ac
STRING: In that cute kind of way a girl would when they wanted
to ask for something.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x3de
STRING: [Fal] “Could you help me again like you did the other
day?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x3f4
STRING: [Chris] “I guess it depends on what we're doing. I don't
want to say yes, and then say I can't do it. So... What
did they ask you to do?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x430
STRING: [Fal] “A man would just say yes, no questions asked.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x450
STRING: [Chris] “Only if it's something I can help with.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x466
STRING: That's the whole reason I chased after her.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x48e
STRING: [Fal] “Careful, aren't we? It'll take time to explain, so do
you mind if we go to the classroom first?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x4ae
STRING: [Chris] “That kind of sounds like the point of no return...”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x4e0
STRING: [Fal] “That's the whole idea. Could you wait in front of
the same classroom as last time? I'll go get the key.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x50c
STRING: [Chris] “Wait, I haven't...”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x522
STRING: Even said yes, yet.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x52e
STRING: [Chris] “...”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x544
STRING: Guess I don't have much choice now.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x550
STRING: But there was no way she would try to make me do
something that I wouldn't be able to do.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x566
STRING: I was sure the way she spoke about it was just her way
of teasing me.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x572
STRING: Still, hoping that it would be something simple, I made
my way to the lecture room that we used when we
copied scores that time, and waited for her to
return.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x5c2
STRING: [Chris] “Doesn't feel like we've been away from here
that long, huh?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x5fc
STRING: [Fal] “Did you just read my mind?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x612
STRING: [Chris] “I guess I did.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x628
STRING: It wasn't that I'd actually become able to read her, it
was simply that it really hadn't been a long time since
we were last here.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x63e
STRING: But I had to say, I wasn't expecting to come back to the
lecture rooms so many times.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x654
STRING: [Chris] “You have to work today, right?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x672
STRING: [Fal] “That's right.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x6a0
STRING: It seems that it's always on my busy
days that they need help.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x6b6
STRING: [Chris] “I guess that's a sign of how much they trust you.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x6e8
STRING: [Fal] “That's putting it positively.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x716
STRING: But, I suppose I should
be thankful they didn't ask on a day when
I have practice.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x72c
STRING: [Chris] “Do you mean like on Tuesdays and Thursdays?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x75e
STRING: [Fal] “Yes. Since everyone knows that I have to practice
on those days, they haven't been asking for my help so
much this month.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x77e
STRING: [Chris] “But don't they know that you have your
part-time job?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x7b0
STRING: [Fal] “Well, just like last time, I always end up getting it
done in time, so...”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x7d0
STRING: [Chris] “I should have such problems...”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x802
STRING: [Fal] “Hmph.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x830
STRING: Anyway, if we don't get started, I might
not be able to finish this one on time.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x846
STRING: [Chris] “Alright. So, what do you have to do this time?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x878
STRING: [Fal] “Mm, today I have to write up a draft for a speech.
And it has to be done by tomorrow.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x898
STRING: [Chris] “Okay, I'll be going now!”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x8ca
STRING: [Fal] “Hey, wait!

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x8f8
STRING: It's not the content of the speech that
I need your help with.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x90e
STRING: [Chris] “And by that you mean...?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x940
STRING: [Fal] “I'll think up the speech as I go, so could you write
down what I say?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x960
STRING: [Chris] “I think I can handle that. But the draft for a
speech? That's surprising... Actually, the fact that there's
teachers who would ask that of you is what's
surprising.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x9a6
STRING: [Fal] “I have to admit this is the first time to be given
such little notice,

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x9d4
STRING: but this kind of thing happens a lot.
I'm not bad at it, after all.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x9ea
STRING: I imagined that in this case, “not bad at” actually meant
“pretty good at.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xa00
STRING: I honestly didn't think that the teachers had trusted her
this much.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xa0c
STRING: [Chris] “But... We don't have enough time, right?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xa3e
STRING: [Fal] “Actually, it's not exactly that we don't have
enough time.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xa76
STRING: These kind of speeches are generally all
the same, so it doesn't matter who writes it.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xa8c
STRING: [Chris] “I think I understand.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xabe
STRING: [Fal] “And it's not that I can't finish it after work...

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xaec
STRING: It's
just...”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xb02
STRING: [Chris] “Oh, okay... But what do you mean by ‘it's
just...’?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xb18
STRING: I started to think that the troubled face I thought I had
seen earlier, was indeed what I thought it had been.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xb36
STRING: [Fal] “There's one thing that I'm not good at...”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xb4c
STRING: [Chris] “Wow, even you have something you can't do
well?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xb7e
STRING: [Fal] “Hmph... Of course I do!”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xb94
STRING: [Chris] “I'm kind of relieved to hear that.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xbc6
STRING: [Fal] “Were you under the impression I was good at
everything?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xbdc
STRING: [Chris] “Kind of. But I guess I'm also kind of happy just
that you told me.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xc18
STRING: [Fal] “Oh? Then I guess...

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xc46
STRING: No, it's definitely not okay.
This isn't something I can laugh about.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xc5c
STRING: [Chris] “So, what is this thing that you're not good at?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xc7a
STRING: [Fal] “Handwriting...”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xc90
STRING: [Chris] “Hm?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xcae
STRING: [Fal] “My handwriting... isn't very pleasant to look at.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xcc4
STRING: [Chris] “Your handwriting?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xce2
STRING: [Fal] “Don't repeat it!”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xcf8
STRING: [Chris] “Wait, that's it?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xd2a
STRING: [Fal] “Hey, this isn't a joke.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xd58
STRING: It might not seem like much
to you, but I'm rather bothered by it.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xd6e
STRING: [Chris] “Just how bad is it? I mean, now that you've
started talking about it, I'm kind of curious.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xd96
STRING: [Fal] “Bad enough for me not to want to show anyone...”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xdac
STRING: [Chris] “Huh?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xdde
STRING: [Fal] “I don't want to show anyone!

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xe0c
STRING: Argh,

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xe30
STRING: Look, we
really don't have time, okay?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xe46
STRING: Fal looked kind of cute, trying to hide her
embarrassment by being curt.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xe5c
STRING: Perhaps it was because I had only seen her completely
perfect side so far, but this was like seeing a new Fal.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xe8e
STRING: [Fal] “Alright, are you ready?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xea4
STRING: [Chris] “Aha-ha, yeah, go ahead.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xec2
STRING: [Fal] “First, we'll start with the introduction.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xeda
STRING: She started off with a formulaic greeting, and I wrote
down everything as she continued to speak.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xef0
STRING: I shouldn't have been surprised that she was able to
dictate without faltering.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xf06
STRING: It wasn't as if I had exceptionally beautiful handwriting,
but I had also never been criticized about it.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xf1c
STRING: We made a surprisingly good pair.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xf28
STRING: I was overwhelmingly lacking in various areas compared
to her, however.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xf3c
STRING: [Fal] “Ah, I was just thinking, about that story.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xf52
STRING: [Chris] “Huh?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xf84
STRING: [Fal] “The story I told you just now, about the teacher
back in their student days.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xf9a
STRING: [Chris] “Oh... Sure.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xfcc
STRING: [Fal] “Were you listening to me?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0xfe2
STRING: [Chris] “Of course, I wrote the whole thing down, too.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1014
STRING: [Fal] “I think it would be better if we put the story
towards the start of the speech.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x102a
STRING: [Chris] “How far towards the start are you thinking?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1048
STRING: [Fal] “Straight after the introduction. I think it might help
to keep the students from getting bored.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1068
STRING: [Chris] “Now that you mention it, that's probably a good
idea.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x109a
STRING: [Fal] “Sorry... This means you're going to have to rewrite

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x10b0
STRING: [Chris] “I don't mind. As long as you're not late for work,
it's all good.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x10e2
STRING: [Fal] “Thanks!”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x10f8
STRING: [Chris] “It's starting to sound like you're a perfectionist,
though.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x112a
STRING: [Fal] “I am when doing things for other people. Don't
worry, I'll find a way to thank you.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1140
STRING: [Chris] “Ha-ha, that's okay, you don't need to go out of
your way.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x115e
STRING: [Fal] “So... After adding those changes, we'll need to
adjust some parts that come later.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x117e
STRING: [Chris] “Got it. I'll write those down and make the
changes afterwards.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x11c0
STRING: [Chris] “Phew...”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x11fa
STRING: [Fal] “Okay, I think that's it.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1228
STRING: I'm really sorry that I kind
of dumped the rest on you.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x123e
STRING: [Chris] “As long as it helps!”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1270
STRING: [Fal] “You've been a great help.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x129e
STRING: Listen, I'm going to
need to leave soon...”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x12b4
STRING: [Chris] “Sure thing. What should I do with the speech?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x12e6
STRING: [Fal] “Right, of course. The sooner I hand it in the better,
so I'll do it before I go to work.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1306
STRING: [Chris] “Here you go.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1338
STRING: [Fal] “Thanks. Oh... You have such beautiful
handwriting.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x134e
STRING: [Chris] “That's not true, but... I guess it's not unpleasant
to look at.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1380
STRING: [Fal] “That's so mean!”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1396
STRING: [Chris] “Wait... I didn't mean it like that!”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x13c8
STRING: [Fal] “I know. I'll be sure to pay you back.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x13de
STRING: [Chris] “Hey I said I...”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1410
STRING: [Fal] “I am most definitely going to pay you back.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1426
STRING: [Chris] “You... Took that to heart, didn't you?”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1458
STRING: [Fal] “I wonder? Well... See you tomorrow.”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1486
STRING: [Chris] “Ah...”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x14a4
STRING: Not waiting for my answer, Fal briskly headed out into
the hallway.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x14ba
STRING: We hadn't decided anything about tomorrow's
practice... Or at least I thought we hadn't...

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x14d0
STRING: [Chris] “Tomorrow again, huh...”

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x14e6
STRING: I'd always decided who I would practice with on the
actual day of practice, but perhaps that wasn't the best
approach.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x14fc
STRING: And then...

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x1508
STRING: I became I aware that a part of me was trying to put off
thinking about it until tomorrow, which made me feel
pathetic.

COMMANDS.LABEL: 0x151e
STRING: What to do about practice tomorrow...
